NETHERLANDS COASTGUARD
NAVIGATIONAL WARNING - ADDITIONAL NR. 95 101929 UTC JAN
WAVE HEIGHT WARNING 300CM TSS TERSCHELLING - GERMAN BIGHT
ISSUED AT 101800 UTC JAN
CONTAINER VESSELS WITH A LENGTH OF 100-200M ARE AT RISK
OF LOSING CONTAINERS DURING HEAVY SEA CONDITIONS
IN PARTICULAR FROM A WEST-NORTHWEST TO NORTHERLY
DIRECTION. THESE VESSELS SHOULD ALTER COURSE IF NECESSARY
TO AVOID COMING ABEAM TO THE WAVES AND TAKE OTHER
APPROPRIATE MEASURES TO AVOID LOSING CONTAINERS.
